Response Action for Integration Procedures
Response Action Properties for Integration Procedures

The Response Action ends an Integration Procedure and returns data to the entity that called it. It can also add data to the data JSON or end conditionally. Response Actions are useful for debugging Integration Procedures.

For specific trimming strategies, see Manipulate JSON with the Send/Response Transformations Properties.

For Integration Procedure examples that include at least one Response Action, see Process Arrays Using Loop Blocks, Handle Errors Using Try-Catch Blocks, and Integration Procedure Action for Integration Procedures.

Response Action Properties for Integration Procedures
These properties are unique to or function in a unique manner in Response Actions. The Response Action ends an Integration Procedure and returns data to the entity that called it.
